	   <tr><td colspan=2>there are three wu's items that require nine components, tunic, cloak, and pants.&nbsp;&nbsp;and yeah, verant blew it on this one.  they wanted to fill in the skill gap for tailors so they introduced wu's, and since three of the items require nine components, they upped the slots of the large kit.  They did overlook the fact that they made 10 slot backpacks unprofitable, and after being petitioned by every master tailor who lost the only profitable tailoring item (the only good one anyway), they corrected the mistake by creating the deluxe sewing kit as a fix, only they had to do it quick before the market reaction got too big, and they didn't have time to add the deluxe to any merchants. (this is all opinion, but think about it) I will bet a full set of wu's that the next major patch will find a merchant or two or ten selling the deluxe sewing kits.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
