	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are two known recipes that take 9 items (Wu's fighting tunic and imbued vale studded tunic). The vale tunic has to be made in a special sewing kit that only halflings can use. There are stationary sewing kits in towns, like forges. They looks like white looms, click on the top bar to activate them (maybe other places u can click too).<br><br>Want a 10-slot container for bank? Go to the igloos in Iceclad Ocean to buy a deluxe toolbox. Can't go to velious? Get 2 small pieces of HQ ore (the stacking kind, drops in Runnyeye) and find a halfling smith in Rivervale to make a&nbsp;&nbsp;special "vale sewing kit." <br><br>Personally, I believe that the disappearance from the stores of the "deluxe sewing kit" was a blunder by Verant. It should be obtainable at some location, maybe hard to get to, like the igloos in Iceclad Ocean, or the brownie camp in Lesser Faydark. It should not have been fouled up like this for future tailors.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
